    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="453"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 8430–1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 231.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose you herewith a copy
                    and translation of the executive decree by which Pampatar, Island of Margarita,
                    is made an open port.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William W. Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="1248" n="1098" xml:id="pg_1098"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>[Inclosure.—Translation.]</head>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="italic">General Cipriano Castro, restorer of Venezuela, and
                            constitutional President of the Republic, in exercise of the powers with
                            which I am vested:</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">decree.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <list>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> 1. The port of Pampatar is hereby
                            constituted the only open port for the importation and exportation of
                            the Island of Margarita, in accordance with the provisions of article
                            20, Law XIV of the Hacienda Code.</item>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Art</hi>. 2. The ultramarine period given in
                            article 225, Law XVI of the Hacienda Code, and counting from the date
                            herewith, is granted for the purposes of carrying out this decree; and
                            at the end of said period the custom-house at Pampatar shall proceed to
                            collect import duties, the same as the other open ports of the
                            Republic.</item>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Art</hi>. 3. The executive decree of April 5, 1905,
                            is hereby annulled.</item>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Art</hi>. 4. The minister of hacienda and public
                            credit is charged with the execution of this decree.</item>
                    </list>
                    <p>Given, signed, sealed, etc., etc., etc.</p>
                    <closer>(Signed) <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cipriano Castro.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
